      "description": "This investment-grade 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S represents the pinnacle of the 996 generation. The 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six features a documented IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement, ensuring long-term mechanical integrity. Power is delivered through a tactile 6-speed manual gearbox and a viscous-coupling AWD system for superior lateral grip and high-speed stability. The chassis is enhanced with corner-balanced Bilstein PSS10 coilovers, while the braking system utilizes four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors for fade-free deceleration. With a clean DME report and zero bore scoring, this specimen offers unparalleled throttle response and turn-in precision for the discerning purist.",
